The paper proposes a novel approach for representation learning in machine learning, specifically for classification and clustering tasks. The approach involves learning a set of high-level features based on the representation of error. This falls under the category of deep learning and representation learning, which are covered in several sub-categories of computer science such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Given the focus on deep learning and representation learning, these sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
